On remote server
 
    enable the password authentication - sudo vim /etc/ssh/sshd_config - PasswordAuthentication yes
    Assign password to the user - sudo passwd root
    restart the sshd service - systemctl restart sshd

On host server
  generate the ssh key - ssh-keygen
  copy the ssh key to remote machine - ssh-copy-id root@ip of remote
   
On remote server
 
     1. Assign the password to the user
     2. enable the password authentication
     3. Restart the sshd

On host machine
 
    1. generate the ssh key
    2 copy the ssh key to remote machine
